# Ibanez TS9 Tube Screamer — netlist source of truth.
#
# Traced from R.G. Keen's "TS-9, -10, -808 Signal Path" schematic (geofex.com, mirrored at
# schematicheaven.net); cross-checked against the ElectroSmash Tube Screamer analysis.
# See REFERENCE.md in this directory for the stage-by-stage ground truth, pot tapers,
# corner frequencies, and what is / is not modeled.
#
# circuitc/netlist.py provides the MODELED component values to the discretizer today. The
# symbolic Lcapy MNA front-end (later) will parse this netlist into the same component set.
# Node 0 is ground (AC ground includes the +4.5V Vref rail). Pot wipers split as
# Rpot1 = Rpot*w, Rpot2 = Rpot*(1-w).
#
# === input buffer (NOT modeled: corners are sub-20 Hz; see REFERENCE.md) ===
# IN -> 0.02u coupling -> 1k series -> Q1 base (510k bias to Vref), emitter follower,
# 10k emitter load -> 1u NP coupling -> A1 noninverting input (10k bias to Vref).
#Cin    in     b1      0.02u
#Rin    b1     b2      1k
#Rbias1 b2     0       510k     # to +4.5V Vref
#Q1     b2     e1      2SC1815  # emitter follower
#Re1    e1     0       10k
#Cc1    e1     in_a    1u       # NP
#Rbias2 in_a   0       10k      # to +4.5V Vref
#
# === drive / clipping stage (MODELED: drive biquad + asinh waveshaper) ===
# Non-inverting op-amp (A1, RC4558 half). Feedback: (51k + 500KA drive pot) || 51p || diodes.
# Inverting leg to AC ground: 4.7k + 0.047u (720 Hz gain shelf).
R1     in_a   a       4700
C1     a      0       0.047u
Rf_d   a      out_d   51k       # series feedback resistor
Rpot_d a      out_d   500k      # drive pot, full value (500KA, audio taper)
Cf     a      out_d   51p       # feedback cap
# Clipping diodes across the feedback path: 2x 1S1588 silicon (~1N4148). Split out as the
# asinh waveshaper stage: Is = 2.52n, n*Vt = 45.3m (standard 1N4148 SPICE model).
#
# === tone control + recovery stage (MODELED: tone biquad) ===
# A1 out -> 1k series -> node t (0.22u to ground = 723 Hz LPF; 10k bias to Vref).
# Tone pot (20KG) end H = node t = A2 noninverting input; end J = A2 inverting input with
# 1k feedback from A2 out; wiper -> 0.22u + 220R series to ground (3.3 kHz boost leg).
R1k    out_d  t       1k        # series from clipping stage
Ctone  t      0       0.22u     # LPF cap at node t
R10k   t      0       10k       # bias to +4.5V Vref (AC ground)
Rpot_t t      w       20k       # tone pot (20KG); t = end H, w = wiper, j = end J
C4     w      cw      0.22u     # wiper boost leg
R220   cw     0       220
Rf_t   j      out_t   1k        # A2 feedback; A2 forces V(j) = V(t)
#
# === level / output buffer (NOT modeled; see REFERENCE.md) ===
# A2 out -> 1u NP -> 1k -> LEVEL pot 100KB (other end to Vref), wiper -> 0.1u -> Q2 base
# (510k bias), emitter follower, 10k emitter load -> 470R series -> 10u/16V -> jack,
# 100k to ground. (TS808 differs here only: 100R series / 10k shunt, and RC4558 vs TA75558.)
#Clev   out_t  l1      1u       # NP
#Rlev   l1     l2      1k
#RpotL  l2     0       100k     # level pot (100KB, linear), end M to Vref
#Cq2    l2w    b3      0.1u     # wiper -> output buffer
#Rbias3 b3     0       510k     # to +4.5V Vref
#Q2     b3     e2      2SC1815  # emitter follower
#Re2    e2     0       10k
#Rout   e2     o1      470      # TS9 (TS808: 100)
#Cout   o1     out     10u
#Rpull  out    0       100k     # TS9 (TS808: 10k)
